Fields.Name: EncodedTextLen
Fields.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedText (355) field.

Fields.Name: EncodedText
Fields.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Text (58) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Text field.

Fields.Name: EncodedSubjectLen
Fields.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSubject (357) field.

Fields.Name: EncodedSubject
Fields.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Subject (147) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Subject field.

Fields.Name: EncodedHeadlineLen
Fields.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedHeadline (359) field.

Fields.Name: EncodedHeadline
Fields.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Headline (148) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Headline field.

Fields.Name: EncodedAllocTextLen
Fields.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedAllocText (361) field.

Fields.Name: EncodedAllocText
Fields.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the AllocText (161) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the AllocText field.

Fields.Name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuerLen
Fields.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingIssuer (363) field.

Fields.Name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuer
Fields.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingIssuer (306) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingIssuer field.

Fields.Name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDescLen
Fields.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc (365) field.

Fields.Name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc
Fields.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingSecurityDesc (307) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingSecurityeDesc field.

Fields.Name: AllocPrice
Fields.Description: Executed price for an AllocAccount (79) entry used when using "executed price" vs. "average price" allocations (e.g. Japan).

Fields.Name: QuoteSetValidUntilTime
Fields.Description: Indicates expiration time of this particular QuoteSet (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Fields.Name: QuoteEntryRejectReason
Fields.Description: Reason Quote Entry was rejected:

Fields.Name: LastMsgSeqNumProcessed
Fields.Description: The last MsgSeqNum (34) value received by the FIX engine and processed by downstream application, such as trading engine or order routing system. Can be specified on every message sent. Useful for detecting a backlog with a counterparty.

Fields.Name: RefTagID
Fields.Description: The tag number of the FIX field being referenced.

Fields.Name: RefMsgType
Fields.Description: The MsgType (35) of the FIX message being referenced.

Fields.Name: SessionRejectReason
Fields.Description: Code to identify reason for a session-level Reject message.

Fields.Name: BidRequestTransType
Fields.Description: Identifies the Bid Request message type.

Fields.Name: ContraBroker
Fields.Description: Identifies contra broker. Standard NASD market-maker mnemonic is preferred.

Fields.Name: ComplianceID
Fields.Description: ID used to represent this transaction for compliance purposes (e.g. OATS reporting).

Fields.Name: SolicitedFlag
Fields.Description: Indicates whether or not the order was solicited.

Fields.Name: ExecRestatementReason
Fields.Description: Code to identify reason for an ExecutionRpt message sent with ExecType=Restated or used when communicating an unsolicited cancel.

Fields.Name: BusinessRejectRefID
Fields.Description: The value of the business-level "ID" field on the message being referenced.

Fields.Name: BusinessRejectReason
Fields.Description: Code to identify reason for a Business Message Reject message.

Fields.Name: GrossTradeAmt
Fields.Description: Total amount traded (i.e. quantity * price) expressed in units of currency. For FX Futures this is used to express the notional value of a fill when quantity fields are expressed in terms of contract size (i.e. quantity * price * contract size).

Fields.Name: NoContraBrokers
Fields.Description: The number of ContraBroker (375) entries.

Fields.Name: MaxMessageSize
Fields.Description: Maximum number of bytes supported for a single message.

Fields.Name: NoMsgTypes
Fields.Description: Number of MsgTypes (35) in repeating group.

Fields.Name: MsgDirection
Fields.Description: Specifies the direction of the messsage.

Fields.Name: NoTradingSessions
Fields.Description: Number of TradingSessionIDs (336) in repeating group.

Fields.Name: TotalVolumeTraded
Fields.Description: Total volume (quantity) traded.

Fields.Name: DiscretionInst
Fields.Description: Code to identify the price a DiscretionOffsetValue (389) is related to and should be mathematically added to.

Fields.Name: DiscretionOffsetValue
Fields.Description: Amount (signed) added to the "related to" price specified via DiscretionInst (388), in the context of DiscretionOffsetType (842) (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was of type PriceOffset)

Fields.Name: BidID
Fields.Description: Unique identifier for Bid Response as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

Fields.Name: ClientBidID
Fields.Description: Unique identifier for a Bid Request as assigned by institution. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

Fields.Name: ListName
Fields.Description: Descriptive name for list order.

Fields.Name: TotNoRelatedSym
Fields.Description: Total number of securities. (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was named TotalNumSecurities)

Fields.Name: BidType
Fields.Description: Code to identify the type of Bid Request.

Fields.Name: NumTickets
Fields.Description: Total number of tickets.

Fields.Name: SideValue1
Fields.Description: Amounts in currency

Fields.Name: SideValue2
Fields.Description: Amounts in currency

Fields.Name: NoBidDescriptors
Fields.Description: Number of BidDescriptor (400) entries.

Fields.Name: BidDescriptorType
Fields.Description: Code to identify the type of BidDescriptor (400).

Fields.Name: BidDescriptor
Fields.Description: BidDescriptor value. Usage depends upon BidDescriptorTyp (399). If BidDescriptorType = 1 Industrials etc - Free text If BidDescriptorType = 2 "FR" etc - ISO Country Codes If BidDescriptorType = 3 FT00, FT250, STOX - Free text

Fields.Name: SideValueInd
Fields.Description: Code to identify which "SideValue" the value refers to. SideValue1 and SideValue2 are used as opposed to Buy or Sell so that the basket can be quoted either way as Buy or Sell.

Fields.Name: LiquidityPctLow
Fields.Description: Liquidity indicator or lower limit if TotalNumSecurities (393) > 1. Represented as a percentage.

Fields.Name: LiquidityPctHigh
Fields.Description: Upper liquidity indicator if TotalNumSecurities (393) > 1. Represented as a percentage.

Fields.Name: LiquidityValue
Fields.Description: Value between LiquidityPctLow (402) and LiquidityPctHigh (403) in Currency

Fields.Name: EFPTrackingError
Fields.Description: Eg Used in EFP trades 2% (EFP - Exchange for Physical ). Represented as a percentage.

Fields.Name: FairValue
Fields.Description: Used in EFP trades

Fields.Name: OutsideIndexPct
Fields.Description: Used in EFP trades. Represented as a percentage.

Fields.Name: ValueOfFutures
Fields.Description: Used in EFP trades

Fields.Name: LiquidityIndType
Fields.Description: Code to identify the type of liquidity indicator.

Fields.Name: WtAverageLiquidity
Fields.Description: Overall weighted average liquidity expressed as a % of average daily volume. Represented as a percentage.

Fields.Name: ExchangeForPhysical
Fields.Description: Indicates whether or not to exchange for phsyical.

Fields.Name: OutMainCntryUIndex
Fields.Description: Value of stocks in Currency

Fields.Name: CrossPercent
Fields.Description: Percentage of program that crosses in Currency. Represented as a percentage.

Fields.Name: ProgRptReqs
Fields.Description: Code to identify the desired frequency of progress reports.

Fields.Name: ProgPeriodInterval
Fields.Description: Time in minutes between each ListStatus report sent by SellSide. Zero means don't send status.

Fields.Name: IncTaxInd
Fields.Description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

Fields.Name: NumBidders
Fields.Description: Indicates the total number of bidders on the list

Fields.Name: BidTradeType
Fields.Description: Code to represent the type of trade. (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was named "TradeType")

Fields.Name: BasisPxType
Fields.Description: Code to represent the basis price type.

Fields.Name: NoBidComponents
Fields.Description: Indicates the number of list entries.

Fields.Name: Country
Fields.Description: ISO Country Code in field

Fields.Name: TotNoStrikes
Fields.Description: Total number of strike price entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoStrikes (428) in each message that has repeating strike price entries related to the same ListID (66). Used to support fragmentation.

Fields.Name: PriceType
Fields.Description: Code to represent the price type. (For Financing transactions PriceType implies the "repo type" - Fixed or Floating - 9 (Yield) or 6 (Spread) respectively - and Price (44) gives the corresponding "repo rate". See Volume : "Glossary" for further value definitions)

Fields.Name: DayOrderQty
Fields.Description: For GT orders, the OrderQty (38) less all quantity (adjusted for stock splits) that traded on previous days. DayOrderQty (424) = OrderQty - (CumQty (14) - DayCumQty (425))

Fields.Name: DayCumQty
Fields.Description: Quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

Fields.Name: DayAvgPx
Fields.Description: The average price for quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

Fields.Name: GTBookingInst
Fields.Description: Code to identify whether to book out executions on a part-filled GT order on the day of execution or to accumulate.

Fields.Name: NoStrikes
Fields.Description: Number of list strike price entries.

Fields.Name: ListStatusType
Fields.Description: Code to represent the status type.

Fields.Name: NetGrossInd
Fields.Description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

Fields.Name: ListOrderStatus
Fields.Description: Code to represent the status of a list order.

Fields.Name: ExpireDate
Fields.Description: Date of order expiration (last day the order can trade), always expressed in terms of the local market date. The time at which the order expires is determined by the local market's business practices

Fields.Name: ListExecInstType
Fields.Description: Identifies the type of ListExecInst (69).

Fields.Name: CxlRejResponseTo
Fields.Description: Identifies the type of request that a Cancel Reject is in response to.

Fields.Name: UnderlyingCouponRate
Fields.Description: Underlying security's CouponRate. See CouponRate (223) field for description

Fields.Name: UnderlyingContractMultiplier
Fields.Description: Underlying security's ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier (231) field for description

Fields.Name: ContraTradeQty
Fields.Description: Quantity traded with the ContraBroker (375).

Fields.Name: ContraTradeTime
Fields.Description: Identifes the time of the trade with the ContraBroker (375). (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Fields.Name: LiquidityNumSecurities
Fields.Description: Number of Securites between LiquidityPctLow (402) and LiquidityPctHigh (403) in Currency.

Fields.Name: MultiLegReportingType
Fields.Description: Used to indicate what an Execution Report represents (e.g. used with multi-leg securities, such as option strategies, spreads, etc.).

Fields.Name: StrikeTime
Fields.Description: The time at which current market prices are used to determine the value of a basket.

Fields.Name: ListStatusText
Fields.Description: Free format text string related to List Status.

Fields.Name: EncodedListStatusTextLen
Fields.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListStatusText (446) field.

Fields.Name: EncodedListStatusText
Fields.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListStatusText (444) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListStatusText field.

Fields.Name: PartyIDSource
Fields.Description: Identifies class or source of the PartyID (448) value. Required if PartyID is specified. Note: applicable values depend upon PartyRole (452) specified. See "Appendix 6-G - Use of <Parties> Component Block"

Fields.Name: PartyID
Fields.Description: Party identifier/code. See PartyIDSource (447) and PartyRole (452). See "Appendix 6-G - Use of <Parties> Component Block"

Fields.Name: NetChgPrevDay
Fields.Description: Net change from previous day's closing price vs. last traded price.

Fields.Name: PartyRole
Fields.Description: Identifies the type or role of the PartyID (448) specified. See "Appendix 6-G - Use of <Parties> Component Block" (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

Fields.Name: NoPartyIDs
Fields.Description: Number of PartyID (448), PartyIDSource (447), and PartyRole (452) entries

Fields.Name: NoSecurityAltID
Fields.Description: Number of SecurityAltID (455) entries.

Fields.Name: SecurityAltID
Fields.Description: Alternate Security identifier value for this security of SecurityAltIDSource (456) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityAltIDSource.

Fields.Name: SecurityAltIDSource
Fields.Description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityAltID (455) value. Required if SecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

Fields.Name: NoUnderlyingSecurityAltID
Fields.Description: Number of UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) entries.

Fields.Name: UnderlyingSecurityAltID
Fields.Description: Alternate Security identifier value for this underlying security of UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource (459) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource.

Fields.Name: UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource
Fields.Description: Identifies class or source of the UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) value. Required if UnderlyingSecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

Fields.Name: Product
Fields.Description: Indicates the type of product the security is associated with. See also the CFICode (461) and SecurityType (167) fields.

Fields.Name: CFICode
Fields.Description: Indicates the type of security using ISO 10962 standard, Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code) values. ISO 10962 is maintained by ANNA (Association of National Numbering Agencies) acting as Registration Authority. See "Appendix 6-B FIX Fields Based Upon Other Standards". See also the Product (460) and SecurityType (167) fields. It is recommended that CFICode be used instead of SecurityType (167) for non-Fixed Income instruments. A subset of possible values applicable to FIX usage are identified in "Appendix 6-D CFICode Usage - ISO 10962 Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code)"

Fields.Name: UnderlyingProduct
Fields.Description: Underlying security's Product. Valid values: see Product(460) field

Fields.Name: UnderlyingCFICode
Fields.Description: Underlying security's CFICode. Valid values: see CFICode (461) field

Fields.Name: TestMessageIndicator
Fields.Description: Indicates whether or not this FIX Session is a "test" vs. "production" connection. Useful for preventing "accidents".

Fields.Name: BookingRefID
Fields.Description: Common reference passed to a post-trade booking process (e.g. industry matching utility).

Fields.Name: IndividualAllocID
Fields.Description: Unique identifier for a specific NoAllocs (78) repeating group instance (e.g. for an AllocAccount).

Fields.Name: RoundingDirection
Fields.Description: Specifies which direction to round For CIV - indicates whether or not the quantity of shares/units is to be rounded and in which direction where CashOrdQty (152) or (for CIV only) OrderPercent (516) are specified on an order. The default is for rounding to be at the discretion of the executing broker or fund manager. e.g. for an order specifying CashOrdQty or OrderPercent if the calculated number of shares/units was 325.76 and RoundingModulus (469) was 0 - "round down" would give 320 units, 1 - "round up" would give 330 units and "round to nearest" would give 320 units.

Fields.Name: RoundingModulus
Fields.Description: For CIV - a float value indicating the value to which rounding is required. i.e. 0 means round to a multiple of 0 units/shares; 0.5 means round to a multiple of 0.5 units/shares. The default, if RoundingDirection (468) is specified without RoundingModulus, is to round to a whole unit/share.

Fields.Name: CountryOfIssue
Fields.Description: ISO Country code of instrument issue (e.g. the country portion typically used in ISIN). Can be used in conjunction with non-ISIN SecurityID (48) (e.g. CUSIP for Municipal Bonds without ISIN) to provide uniqueness.

Fields.Name: StateOrProvinceOfIssue
Fields.Description: A two-character state or province abbreviation.

Fields.Name: LocaleOfIssue
Fields.Description: Identifies the locale. For Municipal Security Issuers other than state or province. Refer to http://www.atmos.albany.edu/cgi/stagrep-cgi Reference the IATA city codes for values. Note IATA (International Air Transport Association) maintains the codes at www.iata.org.

Fields.Name: NoRegistDtls
Fields.Description: The number of registration details on a Registration Instructions message

Fields.Name: MailingDtls
Fields.Description: Set of Correspondence address details, possibly including phone, fax, etc.

Fields.Name: InvestorCountryOfResidence
Fields.Description: The ISO 366 Country code (2 character) identifying which country the beneficial investor is resident for tax purposes.

Fields.Name: PaymentRef
Fields.Description: "Settlement Payment Reference" - A free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation, e.g. a Client and/or Order ID number.

Fields.Name: DistribPaymentMethod
Fields.Description: A code identifying the payment method for a (fractional) distribution. 13 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

Fields.Name: CashDistribCurr
Fields.Description: Specifies currency to be used for Cash Distributions see "Appendix 6-A Valid Currency Codes".

Fields.Name: CommCurrency
Fields.Description: Specifies currency to be use for Commission (12) if the Commission currency is different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

Fields.Name: CancellationRights
Fields.Description: For CIV - A one character code identifying whether Cancellation rights/Cooling off period applies.

Fields.Name: MoneyLaunderingStatus
Fields.Description: A one character code identifying Money laundering status.

Fields.Name: MailingInst
Fields.Description: Free format text to specify mailing instruction requirements, e.g. "no third party mailings".

Fields.Name: TransBkdTime
Fields.Description: For CIV A date and time stamp to indicate the time a CIV order was booked by the fund manager. For derivatives a date and time stamp to indicate when this order was booked with the agent prior to submission to the VMU. Indicates the time at which the order was finalized between the buyer and seller prior to submission.

Fields.Name: ExecPriceType
Fields.Description: For CIV - Identifies how the execution price LastPx (31) was calculated from the fund unit/share price(s) calculated at the fund valuation point.

Fields.Name: ExecPriceAdjustment
Fields.Description: For CIV the amount or percentage by which the fund unit/share price was adjusted, as indicated by ExecPriceType (484)

Fields.Name: DateOfBirth
Fields.Description: The date of birth applicable to the individual, e.g. required to open some types of tax-exempt account.

Fields.Name: TradeReportTransType
Fields.Description: Identifies Trade Report message transaction type (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was of type char)

Fields.Name: CardHolderName
Fields.Description: The name of the payment card holder as specified on the card being used for payment.

Fields.Name: CardNumber
Fields.Description: The number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

Fields.Name: CardExpDate
Fields.Description: The expiry date of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

Fields.Name: CardIssNum
Fields.Description: The issue number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment. This is only applicable to certain types of card.

Fields.Name: PaymentMethod
Fields.Description: A code identifying the Settlement payment method. 16 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

Fields.Name: RegistAcctType
Fields.Description: For CIV - a fund manager-defined code identifying which of the fund manager's account types is required.

Fields.Name: Designation
Fields.Description: Free format text defining the designation to be associated with a holding on the register. Used to identify assets of a specific underlying investor using a common registration, e.g. a broker's nominee or street name.

Fields.Name: TaxAdvantageType
Fields.Description: For CIV - a code identifying the type of tax exempt account in which purchased shares/units are to be held. 30 - 998 are reserved for future use by recognized taxation authorities 999=Other values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

Fields.Name: RegistRejReasonText
Fields.Description: Text indicating reason(s) why a Registration Instruction has been rejected.

Fields.Name: FundRenewWaiv
Fields.Description: A one character code identifying whether the Fund based renewal commission is to be waived.

Fields.Name: CashDistribAgentName
Fields.Description: Name of local agent bank if for cash distributions

Fields.Name: CashDistribAgentCode
Fields.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of agent bank for cash distributions

Fields.Name: CashDistribAgentAcctNumber
Fields.Description: Account number at agent bank for distributions.

Fields.Name: CashDistribPayRef
Fields.Description: Free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation of distributions.

Fields.Name: CashDistribAgentAcctName
Fields.Description: Name of account at agent bank for distributions.

Fields.Name: CardStartDate
Fields.Description: The start date of the card as specified on the card being used for payment.

Fields.Name: PaymentDate
Fields.Description: The date written on a cheque or date payment should be submitted to the relevant clearing system.

Fields.Name: PaymentRemitterID
Fields.Description: Identifies sender of a payment, e.g. the payment remitter or a customer reference number.

Fields.Name: RegistStatus
Fields.Description: Registration status as returned by the broker or (for CIV) the fund manager:

Fields.Name: RegistRejReasonCode
Fields.Description: Reason(s) why Registration Instructions has been rejected. The reason may be further amplified in the RegistRejReasonCode field. Possible values of reason code include:

Fields.Name: RegistRefID
Fields.Description: Reference identifier for the RegistID (53) with Cancel and Replace RegistTransType (54) transaction types.

Fields.Name: RegistDtls
Fields.Description: Set of Registration name and address details, possibly including phone, fax etc.

Fields.Name: NoDistribInsts
Fields.Description: The number of Distribution Instructions on a Registration Instructions message

Fields.Name: RegistEmail
Fields.Description: Email address relating to Registration name and address details

Fields.Name: DistribPercentage
Fields.Description: The amount of each distribution to go to this beneficiary, expressed as a percentage

Fields.Name: RegistID
Fields.Description: Unique identifier of the registration details as assigned by institution or intermediary.

Fields.Name: RegistTransType
Fields.Description: Identifies Registration Instructions transaction type

Fields.Name: ExecValuationPoint
Fields.Description: For CIV - a date and time stamp to indicate the fund valuation point with respect to which a order was priced by the fund manager.

Fields.Name: OrderPercent
Fields.Description: For CIV specifies the approximate order quantity desired. For a CIV Sale it specifies percentage of investor's total holding to be sold. For a CIV switch/exchange it specifies percentage of investor's cash realised from sales to be re-invested. The executing broker, intermediary or fund manager is responsible for converting and calculating OrderQty (38) in shares/units for subsequent messages.

Fields.Name: OwnershipType
Fields.Description: The relationship between Registration parties.

Fields.Name: NoContAmts
Fields.Description: The number of Contract Amount details on an Execution Report message

Fields.Name: ContAmtType
Fields.Description: Type of ContAmtValue (520). NOTE That Commission Amount / % in Contract Amounts is the commission actually charged, rather than the commission instructions given in Fields 2/3.

Fields.Name: ContAmtValue
Fields.Description: Value of Contract Amount, e.g. a financial amount or percentage as indicated by ContAmtType (519).

Fields.Name: ContAmtCurr
Fields.Description: Specifies currency for the Contract amount if different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

Fields.Name: OwnerType
Fields.Description: Identifies the type of owner.

Fields.Name: PartySubID
Fields.Description: Sub-identifier (e.g. Clearing Account for PartyRole (452)=Clearing Firm, Locate ID # for PartyRole=Locate/Lending Firm, etc). Not required when using PartyID (448), PartyIDSource (447), and PartyRole.

Fields.Name: NestedPartyID
Fields.Description: PartyID value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

Fields.Name: NestedPartyIDSource
Fields.Description: PartyIDSource value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

Fields.Name: SecondaryClOrdID
Fields.Description: Assigned by the party which originates the order. Can be used to provide the ClOrdID (11) used by an exchange or executing system.

Fields.Name: SecondaryExecID
Fields.Description: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the ExecID (17) used by an exchange or executing system.

Fields.Name: OrderCapacity
Fields.Description: Designates the capacity of the firm placing the order. (as of FIX 4.3, this field replaced Rule80A (tag 47) --used in conjunction with OrderRestrictions (529) field) (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

Fields.Name: OrderRestrictions
Fields.Description: Restrictions associated with an order. If more than one restriction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

Fields.Name: MassCancelRequestType
Fields.Description: Specifies scope of Order Mass Cancel Request.

Fields.Name: MassCancelResponse
Fields.Description: Specifies the action taken by counterparty order handling system as a result of the Order Mass Cancel Request

Fields.Name: MassCancelRejectReason
Fields.Description: Reason Order Mass Cancel Request was rejected

Fields.Name: TotalAffectedOrders
Fields.Description: Total number of orders affected by either the OrderMassActionRequest(MsgType=CA) or OrderMassCancelRequest(MsgType=Q).

Fields.Name: NoAffectedOrders
Fields.Description: Number of affected orders in the repeating group of order ids.

Fields.Name: AffectedOrderID
Fields.Description: OrderID (37) of an order affected by a mass cancel request.

Fields.Name: AffectedSecondaryOrderID
Fields.Description: SecondaryOrderID (198) of an order affected by a mass cancel request.

Fields.Name: QuoteType
Fields.Description: Identifies the type of quote. An indicative quote is used to inform a counterparty of a market. An indicative quote does not result directly in a trade. A tradeable quote is submitted to a market and will result directly in a trade against other orders and quotes in a market. A restricted tradeable quote is submitted to a market and within a certain restriction (possibly based upon price or quantity) will automatically trade against orders. Order that do not comply with restrictions are sent to the quote issuer who can choose to accept or decline the order. A counter quote is used in the negotiation model. See Volume 7 - Product: Fixed Income for example usage.

Fields.Name: NestedPartyRole
Fields.Description: PartyRole value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

Fields.Name: NoNestedPartyIDs
Fields.Description: Number of NestedPartyID (524), NestedPartyIDSource (525), and NestedPartyRole (538) entries

Fields.Name: TotalAccruedInterestAmt
Fields.Description: Total Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

Fields.Name: MaturityDate
Fields.Description: Date of maturity.

Fields.Name: UnderlyingMaturityDate
Fields.Description: Underlying security's maturity date. See MaturityDate (541) field for description

Fields.Name: InstrRegistry
Fields.Description: Values may include BIC for the depository or custodian who maintain ownership records, the ISO country code for the location of the record, or the value "ZZ" to specify physical ownership of the security (e.g. stock certificate).

Fields.Name: CashMargin
Fields.Description: Identifies whether an order is a margin order or a non-margin order. This is primarily used when sending orders to Japanese exchanges to indicate sell margin or buy to cover. The same tag could be assigned also by buy-side to indicate the intent to sell or buy margin and the sell-side to accept or reject (base on some validation criteria) the margin request.

Fields.Name: NestedPartySubID
Fields.Description: PartySubID value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

Fields.Name: Scope
Fields.Description: Specifies the market scope of the market data.

Fields.Name: MDImplicitDelete
Fields.Description: Defines how a server handles distribution of a truncated book. Defaults to broker option.

Fields.Name: CrossID
Fields.Description: Identifier for a cross order. Must be unique during a given trading day. Recommend that firms use the order date as part of the CrossID for Good Till Cancel (GT) orders.

Fields.Name: CrossType
Fields.Description: Type of cross being submitted to a market

Fields.Name: CrossPrioritization
Fields.Description: Indicates if one side or the other of a cross order should be prioritized. The definition of prioritization is left to the market. In some markets prioritization means which side of the cross order is applied to the market first. In other markets - prioritization may mean that the prioritized side is fully executed (sometimes referred to as the side being protected).

Fields.Name: OrigCrossID
Fields.Description: CrossID of the previous cross order (NOT the initial cross order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous cross order in Cross Cancel and Cross Cancel/Replace Requests.

Fields.Name: NoSides
Fields.Description: Number of Side repeating group instances.

Fields.Name: Username
Fields.Description: Userid or username.

Fields.Name: Password
Fields.Description: Password or passphrase.

Fields.Name: NoLegs
Fields.Description: Number of InstrumentLeg repeating group instances.

Fields.Name: LegCurrency
Fields.Description: Currency associated with a particular Leg's quantity

Fields.Name: TotNoSecurityTypes
Fields.Description: Used to support fragmentation. Indicates total number of security types when multiple Security Type messages are used to return results.

Fields.Name: NoSecurityTypes
Fields.Description: Number of Security Type repeating group instances.

Fields.Name: SecurityListRequestType
Fields.Description: Identifies the type/criteria of Security List Request

Fields.Name: SecurityRequestResult
Fields.Description: The results returned to a Security Request message

Fields.Name: RoundLot
Fields.Description: The trading lot size of a security

Fields.Name: MinTradeVol
Fields.Description: The minimum trading volume for a security

Fields.Name: MultiLegRptTypeReq
Fields.Description: Indicates the method of execution reporting requested by issuer of the order.

Fields.Name: LegPositionEffect
Fields.Description: PositionEffect for leg of a multileg See PositionEffect (77) field for description

Fields.Name: LegCoveredOrUncovered
Fields.Description: CoveredOrUncovered for leg of a multileg See CoveredOrUncovered (203) field for description

Fields.Name: LegPrice
Fields.Description: Price for leg of a multileg See Price (44) field for description

Fields.Name: TradSesStatusRejReason
Fields.Description: Indicates the reason a Trading Session Status Request was rejected.

Fields.Name: TradeRequestID
Fields.Description: Trade Capture Report Request ID

Fields.Name: TradeRequestType
Fields.Description: Type of Trade Capture Report.

Fields.Name: PreviouslyReported
Fields.Description: Indicates if the trade capture report was previously reported to the counterparty

Fields.Name: TradeReportID
Fields.Description: Unique identifier of trade capture report

Fields.Name: TradeReportRefID
Fields.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types.

Fields.Name: MatchStatus
Fields.Description: The status of this trade with respect to matching or comparison.

Fields.Name: MatchType
Fields.Description: The point in the matching process at which this trade was matched.

Fields.Name: OddLot
Fields.Description: This trade is to be treated as an odd lot If this field is not specified, the default will be "N"

Fields.Name: NoClearingInstructions
Fields.Description: Number of clearing instructions

Fields.Name: ClearingInstruction
Fields.Description: Eligibility of this trade for clearing and central counterparty processing values above 4000 are reserved for agreement between parties

Fields.Name: TradeInputSource
Fields.Description: Type of input device or system from which the trade was entered.

Fields.Name: TradeInputDevice
Fields.Description: Specific device number, terminal number or station where trade was entered

Fields.Name: NoDates
Fields.Description: Number of Date fields provided in date range

Fields.Name: AccountType
Fields.Description: Type of account associated with an order

Fields.Name: CustOrderCapacity
Fields.Description: Capacity of customer placing the order Primarily used by futures exchanges to indicate the CTICode (customer type indicator) as required by the US CFTC (Commodity Futures Trading Commission).

Fields.Name: ClOrdLinkID
Fields.Description: Permits order originators to tie together groups of orders in which trades resulting from orders are associated for a specific purpose, for example the calculation of average execution price for a customer or to associate lists submitted to a broker as waves of a larger program trade.

Fields.Name: MassStatusReqID
Fields.Description: Value assigned by issuer of Mass Status Request to uniquely identify the request

Fields.Name: MassStatusReqType
Fields.Description: Mass Status Request Type

Fields.Name: OrigOrdModTime
Fields.Description: The most recent (or current) modification TransactTime (tag 60) reported on an Execution Report for the order. The OrigOrdModTime is provided as an optional field on Order Cancel Request and Order Cancel Replace Requests to identify that the state of the order has not changed since the request was issued. The use of this approach is not recommended.

Fields.Name: LegSettlType
Fields.Description: Refer to values for SettlType[63]

Fields.Name: LegSettlDate
Fields.Description: Refer to description for SettlDate[64]

Fields.Name: DayBookingInst
Fields.Description: Indicates whether or not automatic booking can occur.

Fields.Name: BookingUnit
Fields.Description: Indicates what constitutes a bookable unit.

Fields.Name: PreallocMethod
Fields.Description: Indicates the method of preallocation.

Fields.Name: UnderlyingCountryOfIssue
Fields.Description: Underlying security's CountryOfIssue. See CountryOfIssue (470) field for description

Fields.Name: UnderlyingStateOrProvinceOfIssue
Fields.Description: Underlying security's StateOrProvinceOfIssue. See StateOrProvinceOfIssue (471) field for description

Fields.Name: UnderlyingLocaleOfIssue
Fields.Description: Underlying security's LocaleOfIssue. See LocaleOfIssue (472) field for description

Fields.Name: UnderlyingInstrRegistry
Fields.Description: Underlying security's InstrRegistry. See InstrRegistry (543) field for description

Fields.Name: LegCountryOfIssue
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's CountryOfIssue. See CountryOfIssue (470) field for description

Fields.Name: LegStateOrProvinceOfIssue
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's StateOrProvinceOfIssue. See StateOrProvinceOfIssue (471) field for description

Fields.Name: LegLocaleOfIssue
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's LocaleOfIssue. See LocaleOfIssue (472) field for description

Fields.Name: LegInstrRegistry
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's InstrRegistry. See InstrRegistry (543) field for description

Fields.Name: LegSymbol
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's Symbol. See Symbol (55) field for description

Fields.Name: LegSymbolSfx
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's SymbolSfx. See SymbolSfx (65) field for description

Fields.Name: LegSecurityID
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's SecurityID. See SecurityID (48) field for description

Fields.Name: LegSecurityIDSource
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's SecurityIDSource. See SecurityIDSource (22) field for description

Fields.Name: NoLegSecurityAltID
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's NoSecurityAltID. See NoSecurityAltID (454) field for description

Fields.Name: LegSecurityAltID
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's SecurityAltID. See SecurityAltID (455) field for description

Fields.Name: LegSecurityAltIDSource
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's SecurityAltIDSource. See SecurityAltIDSource (456) field for description

Fields.Name: LegProduct
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's Product. See Product (460) field for description

Fields.Name: LegCFICode
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's CFICode. See CFICode (461) field for description

Fields.Name: LegSecurityType
Fields.Description: Refer to definition of SecurityType(167)

Fields.Name: LegMaturityMonthYear
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's MaturityMonthYear. See MaturityMonthYear (200) field for description

Fields.Name: LegMaturityDate
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's MaturityDate. See MaturityDate (54) field for description

Fields.Name: LegStrikePrice
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's StrikePrice. See StrikePrice (202) field for description

Fields.Name: LegOptAttribute
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's OptAttribute. See OptAttribute (206) field for description

Fields.Name: LegContractMultiplier
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier (23) field for description

Fields.Name: LegCouponRate
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's CouponRate. See CouponRate (223) field for description

Fields.Name: LegSecurityExchange
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's SecurityExchange. See SecurityExchange (207) field for description

Fields.Name: LegIssuer
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's Issuer. See Issuer (106) field for description

Fields.Name: EncodedLegIssuerLen
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's EncodedIssuerLen. See EncodedIssuerLen (348) field for description

Fields.Name: EncodedLegIssuer
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's EncodedIssuer. See EncodedIssuer (349) field for description

Fields.Name: LegSecurityDesc
Fields.Description: Description of a leg of a multileg instrument. See SecurityDesc(107).

Fields.Name: EncodedLegSecurityDescLen
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's EncodedSecurityDescLen. See EncodedSecurityDescLen (350) field for description

Fields.Name: EncodedLegSecurityDesc
Fields.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's EncodedSecurityDesc. See EncodedSecurityDesc (35) field for description

Fields.Name: LegRatioQty
Fields.Description: The ratio of quantity for this individual leg relative to the entire multileg security.

Fields.Name: LegSide
Fields.Description: The side of this individual leg (multileg security). See Side (54) field for description and values

Fields.Name: TradingSessionSubID
Fields.Description: Optional market assigned sub identifier for a trading phase within a trading session. Usage is determined by market or counterparties. Used by US based futures markets to identify exchange specific execution time bracket codes as required by US market regulations. Bilaterally agreed values of data type "String" that start with a character can be used for backward compatibility

Fields.Name: AllocType
Fields.Description: Describes the specific type or purpose of an Allocation message (i.e. "Buyside Calculated") (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions) *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

Fields.Name: NoHops
Fields.Description: Number of HopCompID entries in repeating group.

Fields.Name: HopCompID
Fields.Description: Assigned value used to identify the third party firm which delivered a specific message either from the firm which originated the message or from another third party (if multiple "hops" are performed). It is recommended that this value be the SenderCompID (49) of the third party. Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or "hubs". Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

Fields.Name: HopSendingTime
Fields.Description: Time that HopCompID (628) sent the message. It is recommended that this value be the SendingTime (52) of the message sent by the third party. Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or "hubs". Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

Fields.Name: HopRefID
Fields.Description: Reference identifier assigned by HopCompID (628) associated with the message sent. It is recommended that this value be the MsgSeqNum (34) of the message sent by the third party. Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or "hubs". Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

Fields.Name: MidPx
Fields.Description: Mid price/rate

Fields.Name: BidYield
Fields.Description: Bid yield

Fields.Name: MidYield
Fields.Description: Mid yield

Fields.Name: OfferYield
Fields.Description: Offer yield

Fields.Name: ClearingFeeIndicator
Fields.Description: Indicates type of fee being assessed of the customer for trade executions at an exchange. Applicable for futures markets only at this time. (Values source CBOT, CME, NYBOT, and NYMEX):

Fields.Name: WorkingIndicator
Fields.Description: Indicates if the order is currently being worked. Applicable only for OrdStatus = "New". For open outcry markets this indicates that the order is being worked in the crowd. For electronic markets it indicates that the order has transitioned from a contingent order to a market order.

Fields.Name: LegLastPx
Fields.Description: Execution price assigned to a leg of a multileg instrument. See LastPx (31) field for description and values

Fields.Name: PriorityIndicator
Fields.Description: Indicates if a Cancel/Replace has caused an order to lose book priority.

Fields.Name: PriceImprovement
Fields.Description: Amount of price improvement.

Fields.Name: Price2
Fields.Description: Price of the future part of a F/X swap order. See Price (44) for description.

Fields.Name: LastForwardPoints2
Fields.Description: F/X forward points of the future part of a F/X swap order added to LastSpotRate (94). May be a negative value.

Fields.Name: BidForwardPoints2
Fields.Description: Bid F/X forward points of the future portion of a F/X swap quote added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Fields.Name: OfferForwardPoints2
Fields.Description: Offer F/X forward points of the future portion of a F/X swap quote added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Fields.Name: RFQReqID
Fields.Description: RFQ Request ID - used to identify an RFQ Request.

Fields.Name: MktBidPx
Fields.Description: Used to indicate the best bid in a market

Fields.Name: MktOfferPx
Fields.Description: Used to indicate the best offer in a market

Fields.Name: MinBidSize
Fields.Description: Used to indicate a minimum quantity for a bid. If this field is used the BidSize (134) field is interpreted as the maximum bid size

Fields.Name: MinOfferSize
Fields.Description: Used to indicate a minimum quantity for an offer. If this field is used the OfferSize (135) field is interpreted as the maximum offer size.

Fields.Name: QuoteStatusReqID
Fields.Description: Unique identifier for Quote Status Request.

Fields.Name: LegalConfirm
Fields.Description: Indicates that this message is to serve as the final and legal confirmation.

Fields.Name: UnderlyingLastPx
Fields.Description: The calculated or traded price for the underlying instrument that corresponds to a derivative. Used for transactions that include the cash instrument and the derivative.

Fields.Name: UnderlyingLastQty
Fields.Description: The calculated or traded quantity for the underlying instrument that corresponds to a derivative. Used for transactions that include the cash instrument and the derivative.

Fields.Name: LegRefID
Fields.Description: Unique indicator for a specific leg.

Fields.Name: ContraLegRefID
Fields.Description: Unique indicator for a specific leg for the ContraBroker (375).

Fields.Name: SettlCurrBidFxRate
Fields.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute the bid "SettlCurrAmt" (119) from Currency (15) to SettlCurrency (120)

Fields.Name: SettlCurrOfferFxRate
Fields.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute the offer "SettlCurrAmt" (119) from Currency (15) to SettlCurrency (120)

Fields.Name: QuoteRequestRejectReason
Fields.Description: Reason Quote was rejected:

Fields.Name: SideComplianceID
Fields.Description: ID within repeating group of sides which is used to represent this transaction for compliance purposes (e.g. OATS reporting).

Fields.Name: AcctIDSource
Fields.Description: Used to identify the source of the Account (1) code. This is especially useful if the account is a new account that the Respondent may not have setup yet in their system.

Fields.Name: AllocAcctIDSource
Fields.Description: Used to identify the source of the AllocAccount (79) code. See AcctIDSource (660) for valid values.

Fields.Name: BenchmarkPrice
Fields.Description: Specifies the price of the benchmark.

Fields.Name: BenchmarkPriceType
Fields.Description: Identifies type of BenchmarkPrice (662). See PriceType (423) for valid values.

Fields.Name: ConfirmID
Fields.Description: Message reference for Confirmation

Fields.Name: ConfirmStatus
Fields.Description: Identifies the status of the Confirmation.

Fields.Name: ConfirmTransType
Fields.Description: Identifies the Confirmation transaction type.

Fields.Name: ContractSettlMonth
Fields.Description: Specifies when the contract (i.e. MBS/TBA) will settle.

Fields.Name: DeliveryForm
Fields.Description: Identifies the form of delivery.

Fields.Name: LastParPx
Fields.Description: Last price expressed in percent-of-par. Conditionally required for Fixed Income trades when LastPx (31) is expressed in Yield, Spread, Discount or any other type. Usage: Execution Report and Allocation Report repeating executions block (from sellside).

Fields.Name: NoLegAllocs
Fields.Description: Number of Allocations for the leg

Fields.Name: LegAllocAccount
Fields.Description: Allocation Account for the leg See AllocAccount (79) for description and valid values.

Fields.Name: LegIndividualAllocID
Fields.Description: Reference for the individual allocation ticket See IndividualAllocID (467) for description and valid values.

Fields.Name: LegAllocQty
Fields.Description: Leg allocation quantity. See AllocQty (80) for description and valid values.

Fields.Name: LegAllocAcctIDSource
Fields.Description: The source of the LegAllocAccount (671) See AllocAcctIDSource (661) for description and valid values.

Fields.Name: LegSettlCurrency
Fields.Description: Identifies settlement currency for the Leg. See SettlCurrency (20) for description and valid values

Fields.Name: LegBenchmarkCurveCurrency
Fields.Description: LegBenchmarkPrice (679) currency See BenchmarkCurveCurrency (220) for description and valid values.

Fields.Name: LegBenchmarkCurveName
Fields.Description: Name of the Leg Benchmark Curve. See BenchmarkCurveName (22) for description and valid values.

Fields.Name: LegBenchmarkCurvePoint
Fields.Description: Identifies the point on the Leg Benchmark Curve. See BenchmarkCurvePoint (222) for description and valid values.

Fields.Name: LegBenchmarkPrice
Fields.Description: Used to identify the price of the benchmark security. See BenchmarkPrice (662) for description and valid values.

Fields.Name: LegBenchmarkPriceType
Fields.Description: The price type of the LegBenchmarkPrice. See BenchmarkPriceType (663) for description and valid values.

Fields.Name: LegBidPx
Fields.Description: Bid price of this leg. See BidPx (32) for description and valid values.

Fields.Name: LegIOIQty
Fields.Description: Leg-specific IOI quantity. See IOIQty (27) for description and valid values

Fields.Name: NoLegStipulations
Fields.Description: Number of leg stipulation entries

Fields.Name: LegOfferPx
Fields.Description: Offer price of this leg. See OfferPx (133) for description and valid values

Fields.Description: Sub-type qualification/identification of the SecurityType. As an example for SecurityType(167)="REPO", the SecuritySubType="General Collateral" can be used to further specify the type of REPO. If SecuritySubType is used then SecurityType is required. For SecurityType="MLEG" a name of the option or futures strategy name can be specified, such as "Calendar", "Vertical", "Butterfly".

Fields.Name: UnderlyingSecuritySubType

Fields.Name: LegSecuritySubType

Fields.Description: Traded / Regulatory timestamp value. Use to store time information required by government regulators or self regulatory organizations (such as an exchange or clearing house).

Fields.Description: Text which identifies the "origin" (i.e. system which was used to generate the time stamp) for the Traded / Regulatory timestamp value.

Fields.Description: Identifies the type of Confirmation message being sent.

Fields.Name: ConfirmRejReason
Fields.Description: Identifies the reason for rejecting a Confirmation.

Fields.Description: Method for booking out this order. Used when notifying a broker that an order to be settled by that broker is to be booked out as an OTC derivative (e.g. CFD or similar).

Unlike the AllocID (70), this can be shared across a number of allocation instruction or allocation report messages, thereby making it possible to pass an identifier for an original allocation message on multiple messages (e.g. from one party to a second to a third, across cancel and replace messages etc.).

Fields.Description: Type of account associated with a confirmation or other trade-level message

Fields.Name: OrderAvgPx
Fields.Description: Average price for a specific order

Fields.Description: Quantity of the order that is being booked out as part of an Allocation Instruction or Allocation Report message

Fields.Description: Type of Nested2PartySubID (760) value. Second instance of <NestedParties>. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

Fields.Name: NoAltMDSource

Fields.Name: DiscretionPrice

Fields.Name: DiscretionScope
Fields.Description: The scope of the discretion

Fields.Name: TargetStrategyPerformance

Fields.Name: PublishTrdIndicator
Fields.Description: Indicates if a trade should be reported via a market reporting service.

Fields.Name: ShortSaleReason

Fields.Description: Type of quantity specified in a quantity field:

Fields.Name: TradeReportType
Fields.Description: Type of Trade Report

Fields.Name: AllocNoOrdersType
Fields.Description: Indicates how the orders being booked and allocated by an Allocation Instruction or Allocation Report message are identified, i.e. by explicit definition in the NoOrders group or not.

Fields.Name: SharedCommission
Fields.Description: Commission to be shared with a third party, e.g. as part of a directed brokerage commission sharing arrangement.

Fields.Name: ConfirmReqID
Fields.Description: Unique identifier for a Confirmation Request message

Fields.Name: AvgParPx
Fields.Description: Used to express average price as percent of par (used where AvgPx field is expressed in some other way)

Fields.Description: Percent at risk due to lowest possible call.

Fields.Name: NoInstrAttrib
Fields.Description: Number of repeating InstrAttribType entries.

Fields.Name: InstrAttribType
Fields.Description: Code to represent the type of instrument attribute

Fields.Name: InstrAttribValue
Fields.Description: Attribute value appropriate to the InstrAttribType (87) field.

Fields.Name: DatedDate
Fields.Description: The effective date of a new securities issue determined by its underwriters. Often but not always the same as the Issue Date and the Interest Accrual Date

Fields.Description: The start date used for calculating accrued interest on debt instruments which are being sold between interest payment dates. Often but not always the same as the Issue Date and the Dated Date

Fields.Name: UnderlyingCPRegType
Fields.Description: The registration type of the underlying commercial paper issuance

Fields.Name: UnderlyingEndPrice
Fields.Description: Price (percent-of-par or per unit) of the underlying security or basket at the end of the agreement.

Fields.Name: UnderlyingCurrentValue

Fields.Name: UnderlyingStipValue
Fields.Description: Value of stipulation. Same values as StipulationValue (234)

Fields.Name: MaturityNetMoney
Fields.Description: Net Money at maturity if Zero Coupon and maturity value is different from par value

Fields.Name: MiscFeeBasis
Fields.Description: Defines the unit for a miscellaneous fee.

Fields.Name: LastFragment
Fields.Description: Indicates whether this message is the last in a sequence of messages for those messages that support fragmentation, such as Allocation Instruction, Mass Quote, Security List, Derivative Security List

Fields.Name: CollAsgnReason

Fields.Name: CollInquiryQualifier

Fields.Name: MarginExcess
Fields.Description: Excess margin amount (deficit if value is negative)

Fields.Name: TotalNetValue
Fields.Description: TotalNetValue is determined as follows: At the initial collateral assignment TotalNetValue is the sum of (UnderlyingStartValue * (1-haircut)). In a collateral substitution TotalNetValue is the sum of (UnderlyingCurrentValue * (1-haircut)). For listed derivatives clearing margin management, this is the collateral value which equals (Market value * haircut)

Fields.Name: CashOutstanding
Fields.Description: Starting consideration less repayments

Fields.Name: CollAsgnID
Fields.Description: Collateral Assignment Identifier

Fields.Name: CollAsgnTransType

Fields.Name: CollRespID

Fields.Name: CollAsgnRespType
Fields.Description: Collateral Assignment Response Type

Fields.Name: CollAsgnRejectReason

Fields.Name: CollStatus

Fields.Name: LastRptRequested
Fields.Description: Indicates whether this message is that last report message in response to a request, such as Order Mass Status Request.

Fields.Name: AgreementDate
Fields.Description: A reference to the date the underlying agreement specified by AgreementID and AgreementDesc was executed.

Fields.Name: StartDate
Fields.Description: Start date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the buyer pays the seller cash and takes control of the collateral

Fields.Name: EndDate
Fields.Description: End date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the seller reimburses the buyer and takes back control of the collateral

Fields.Name: AgreementCurrency
Fields.Description: Contractual currency forming the basis of a financing agreement and associated transactions. Usually, but not always, the same as the trade currency.

Fields.Name: DeliveryType
Fields.Description: Identifies type of settlement

Fields.Name: EndAccruedInterestAmt
Fields.Description: Accrued Interest Amount applicable to a financing transaction on the End Date.

Fields.Name: EndCash
Fields.Description: Ending dirty cash consideration of a financing deal. i.e. reimbursed to the buyer on the End Date.

Fields.Name: UserRequestID

Fields.Name: UserRequestType
Fields.Description: Indicates the action required by a User Request Message

Fields.Name: NewPassword

Fields.Name: UserStatus
Fields.Description: Indicates the status of a user

Fields.Name: UserStatusText
Fields.Description: A text description associated with a user status.

Fields.Name: StatusValue
Fields.Description: Indicates the status of a network connection

Fields.Name: StatusText
Fields.Description: A text description associated with a network status.

Fields.Name: RefCompID
Fields.Description: Assigned value used to identify a firm.

Fields.Name: RefSubID

Fields.Name: AllocCustomerCapacity

Fields.Name: TierCode

Fields.Name: UnitOfMeasure
Fields.Description: The unit of measure of the underlying commodity upon which the contract is based. Two groups of units of measure enumerations are supported. Fixed Magnitude UOMs are primarily used in energy derivatives and specify a magnitude (such as, MM, Kilo, M, etc.) and the dimension (such as, watt hours, BTU's) to produce standard fixed measures (such as MWh - Megawatt-hours, MMBtu - One million BTUs). The second group, Variable Quantity UOMs, specifies the dimension as a single unit without a magnitude (or more accurately a magnitude of one) and uses the UnitOfMeasureQty(1147) field to define the quantity of units per contract. Variable Quantity UOMs are used for both commodities (such as lbs of lean cattle, bushels of corn, ounces of gold) and financial futures. Examples: For lean cattle futures contracts, a UnitOfMeasure of 'lbs' with a UnitOfMeasureQty(1147) of 40,000, means each lean cattle futures contract represents 40,000 lbs of lean cattle. For Eurodollars futures contracts, a UnitOfMeasure of USD with a UnitOfMeasureQty(1147) of 1,000,000, means a Eurodollar futures contract represents 1,000,000 USD. For gold futures contracts, a UnitOfMeasure is oz_tr (Troy ounce) with a UnitOfMeasureQty(1147) of 1,000, means each gold futures contract represents 1,000 troy ounces of gold.

Fields.Name: TimeUnit
Fields.Description: Unit of time associated with the contract. NOTE: Additional values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties

Fields.Name: UnderlyingUnitOfMeasure

Fields.Name: LegUnitOfMeasure
Fields.Description: Refer to defintion of UnitOfMeasure(996)

Fields.Name: UnderlyingTimeUnit

Fields.Name: MessageEventSource

Fields.Name: AsOfIndicator
Fields.Description: Used to indicate that a floor-trade was originally submitted "as of" a specific trade date which is earlier than its clearing date.

Fields.Name: NoSideTrdRegTS
Fields.Description: Indicates number of SideTimestamps contained in group

Fields.Name: LegOptionRatio
Fields.Description: Expresses the risk of an option leg Value must be between -1 and 1. A Call Option will require a ratio value between 0 and 1 A Put Option will require a ratio value between -1 and 0

Fields.Name: NoInstrumentParties

Fields.Description: PartyID value within an instrument party repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

Fields.Name: TradeVolume
Fields.Description: Used to report volume with a trade

Fields.Name: MDBookType

Fields.Name: MDFeedType
Fields.Description: Describes a class of service for a given data feed, ie Regular and Market Maker, Bandwidth Intensive or Bandwidth Conservative

Fields.Name: MDPriceLevel
Fields.Description: Integer to convey the level of a bid or offer at a given price level. This is in contrast to MDEntryPositionNo which is used to convey the position of an order within a Price level

Fields.Name: MDOriginType

Fields.Name: FirstPx

Fields.Name: MDEntrySpotRate

Fields.Name: MDEntryForwardPoints
Fields.Description: Used for an F/X entry. The forward points to be added to or subtracted from the spot rate to get the "all-in" rate in MDEntryPx. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Fields.Name: ManualOrderIndicator

Fields.Name: DeskType

Fields.Name: DeskTypeSource

Fields.Name: DeskOrderHandlingInst
Fields.Description: Codes that apply special information that the Broker / Dealer needs to report. NOTE: This field and its values have no bearing on the ExecInst and TimeInForce fields. These values should not be used instead of ExecInst or TimeInForce. This field and its values are intended for compliance reporting only. Valid values are grouped by OrderHandlingInstSource(1032).

Fields.Name: ExecAckStatus

Fields.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryAmount

Fields.Name: UnderlyingCapValue

Fields.Name: SecondaryTradeID

Fields.Name: SecondaryFirmTradeID

Fields.Description: Type of underlying InstrumentPartySubID (1053) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

Fields.Name: BidSwapPoints
Fields.Description: The bid FX Swap points for an FX Swap. It is the "far bid forward points - near offer forward point". Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Fields.Name: OfferSwapPoints
Fields.Description: The offer FX Swap points for an FX Swap. It is the "far offer forward points - near bid forward points". Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Fields.Name: LegBidForwardPoints
Fields.Description: The bid FX forward points for the leg of an FX Swap. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Fields.Name: LegOfferForwardPoints
Fields.Description: The offer FX forward points for the leg of an FX Swap. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Fields.Name: SwapPoints
Fields.Description: For FX Swap, this is used to express the differential between the far leg's bid/offer and the near leg's bid/offer. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Fields.Name: MDQuoteType
Fields.Description: Identifies market data quote type.

Fields.Name: LastSwapPoints
Fields.Description: For FX Swap, this is used to express the last market event for the differential between the far leg's bid/offer and the near leg's bid/offer in a fill or partial fill. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Fields.Name: SideGrossTradeAmt
Fields.Description: The gross trade amount for this side of the trade. See also GrossTradeAmt (381) for additional definition.

Fields.Name: LegLastForwardPoints
Fields.Description: The forward points for this leg's fill event. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Fields.Name: LegCalculatedCcyLastQty
Fields.Description: Used for the calculated quantity of the other side of the currency for this leg. Can be derived from LegQty and LegLastPx.

Fields.Name: LegGrossTradeAmt
Fields.Description: The gross trade amount of the leg. For FX Futures this is used to express the notional value of a fill when LegLastQty and other quantity fields are express in terms of contract size.

Fields.Name: MaturityTime
Fields.Description: Time of security's maturity expressed in local time with offset to UTC specified

Fields.Name: RefOrderID
Fields.Description: The ID reference to the order being hit or taken

Fields.Name: RefOrderIDSource
Fields.Description: Used to specify what identifier, provided in order depth market data, to use when hitting (taking) a specific order.

Fields.Name: SecondaryDisplayQty
Fields.Description: Used for reserve orders when DisplayQty applies to the primary execution market (e.g.an ECN) and another quantity is to be shown at other markets (e.g. the exchange). On orders specifies the qty to be displayed, on execution reports the currently displayed quantity.

Fields.Name: DisplayWhen
Fields.Description: Instructs when to refresh DisplayQty (1138).

Fields.Name: DisplayMethod
Fields.Description: Defines what value to use in DisplayQty (1138). If not specified the default DisplayMethod is "1"

Fields.Name: DisplayLowQty
Fields.Description: Defines the lower quantity limit to a randomized refresh of DisplayQty.

Fields.Name: DisplayHighQty
Fields.Description: Defines the upper quantity limit to a randomized refresh of DisplayQty.

Fields.Name: DisplayMinIncr
Fields.Description: Defines the minimum increment to be used when calculating a random refresh of DisplayQty. A user specifies this when he wants a larger increment than the standard provided by the market (e.g. the round lot size).

Fields.Name: RefreshQty
Fields.Description: Defines the quantity used to refresh DisplayQty.

Fields.Name: MatchIncrement
Fields.Description: Allows orders to specify a minimum quantity that applies to every execution (one execution could be for multiple counter-orders). The order may still fill against smaller orders, but the cumulative quantity of the execution must be in multiples of the MatchIncrement.

Fields.Name: MaxPriceLevels
Fields.Description: Allows an order to specify a maximum number of price levels to trade through. Only valid for aggressive orders and during continuous (autoexecution) trading sessions. Property lost when order is put on book. A partially filled order is assigned last trade price as limit price. Non-filled order behaves as ordinary Market or Limit.

Fields.Name: PreTradeAnonymity
Fields.Description: Allows trader to explicitly request anonymity or disclosure in pre-trade market data feeds. Anonymity is relevant in markets where counterparties are regularly disclosed in order depth feeds. Disclosure is relevant when counterparties are not normally visible.

Fields.Name: PriceProtectionScope
Fields.Description: Defines the type of price protection the customer requires on their order.

Fields.Name: LotType
Fields.Description: Defines the lot type assigned to the order.

Fields.Name: PegPriceType
Fields.Description: Defines the type of peg.

Fields.Name: PeggedRefPrice
Fields.Description: The value of the reference price that the order is pegged to. PeggedRefPrice + PegOffsetValue (211) = PeggedPrice (839) unless the limit price (44, Price) is breached. The values may not be exact due to rounding.

Fields.Name: PegSecurityIDSource
Fields.Description: Defines the identity of the security off whose prices the order will peg. Same values as SecurityIDSource (22)

Fields.Name: PegSecurityID
Fields.Description: Defines the identity of the security off whose prices the order will peg.

Fields.Name: PegSymbol
Fields.Description: Defines the common, 'human understood' representation of the security off whose prices the order will Peg.

Fields.Name: PegSecurityDesc
Fields.Description: Security description of the security off whose prices the order will Peg.

Fields.Name: TriggerType
Fields.Description: Defines when the trigger will hit, i.e. the action specified by the trigger instructions will come into effect.

Fields.Name: TriggerAction
Fields.Description: Defines the type of action to take when the trigger hits.

Fields.Name: TriggerPrice
Fields.Description: The price at which the trigger should hit.

Fields.Name: TriggerSymbol
Fields.Description: Defines the common, 'human understood' representation of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

Fields.Name: TriggerSecurityID
Fields.Description: Defines the identity of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

Fields.Name: TriggerSecurityIDSource
Fields.Description: Defines the identity of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic. Same values as SecurityIDSource (22).

Fields.Name: TriggerSecurityDesc
Fields.Description: Defines the security description of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

Fields.Name: TriggerPriceType
Fields.Description: The type of price that the trigger is compared to.

Fields.Name: TriggerPriceTypeScope
Fields.Description: Defines the type of price protection the customer requires on their order.

Fields.Name: TriggerPriceDirection
Fields.Description: The side from which the trigger price is reached.

Fields.Name: TriggerNewPrice

Fields.Name: TriggerOrderType
Fields.Description: The OrdType the order should have after the trigger has hit. Required to express orders that change from Limit to Market. Other values from OrdType (40) may be used if appropriate and bilaterally agreed upon.

Fields.Name: TriggerNewQty
Fields.Description: The Quantity the order should have after the trigger has hit.

Fields.Name: TriggerTradingSessionID
Fields.Description: Defines the trading session at which the order will be activated.

Fields.Name: TriggerTradingSessionSubID
Fields.Description: Defines the subordinate trading session at which the order will be activated.

Fields.Name: OrderCategory
Fields.Description: Defines the type of interest behind a trade (fill or partial fill).

Fields.Name: NoRootPartyIDs
Fields.Description: Number of RootPartyID (1117), RootPartyIDSource (1118), and RootPartyRole (1119) entries

Fields.Name: RootPartyID
Fields.Description: PartyID value within a root parties component. Same values as PartyID (448)

Fields.Name: RootPartyIDSource
Fields.Description: PartyIDSource value within a root parties component. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

Fields.Name: RootPartyRole
Fields.Description: PartyRole value within a root parties component. Same values as PartyRole (452)

Fields.Name: NoRootPartySubIDs
Fields.Description: Number of RootPartySubID (1121) and RootPartySubIDType (1122) entries

Fields.Name: RootPartySubID
Fields.Description: PartySubID value within a root parties component. Same values as PartySubID (523)

Fields.Name: RootPartySubIDType
Fields.Description: Type of RootPartySubID (1121) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

Fields.Name: TradeHandlingInstr
Fields.Description: Specified how the Trade Capture Report should be handled by the Respondent.

Fields.Name: OrigTradeHandlingInstr
Fields.Description: Optionally used with TradeHandlingInstr = 0 to relay the trade handling instruction used when reporting the trade to the marketplace. Same values as TradeHandlingInstr (1123)

Fields.Name: OrigTradeDate
Fields.Description: Used to preserve original trade date when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

Fields.Name: OrigTradeID
Fields.Description: Used to preserve original trade id when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

Fields.Name: OrigSecondaryTradeID
Fields.Description: Used to preserve original secondary trade id when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

Fields.Name: CstmApplVerID
Fields.Description: Specifies a custom extension to a message being applied at the message level. Enumerated field

Fields.Name: RefCstmApplVerID

Fields.Name: TZTransactTime
Fields.Description: Transact time in the local date-time stamp with a TZ offset to UTC identified

Fields.Name: ExDestinationIDSource

Fields.Name: ReportedPxDiff

Fields.Name: RptSys

Fields.Name: AllocClearingFeeIndicator

Fields.Name: DisplayQty
Fields.Description: The quantity to be displayed . Required for reserve orders. On orders specifies the qty to be displayed, on execution reports the currently displayed quantity.

Fields.Name: ExchangeSpecialInstructions
